# Remotion runtime assets live under data/{date}/remotion/ (already covered
# by the data/ rule above): public/ (audio + images + props.json mirror),
# chunks/ (segment cache), single.mp4 (single-shot render temp). The source
# tree under src/providers/renderer/remotion/ is intentionally free of
# runtime output.

# Remotion render output (legacy; new renders go to data/{date}/remotion/)
**/remotion/out/

# Source-tree Remotion public/ stays empty by design — runtime assets flow
# through data/{date}/remotion/public/ (see _remotion_data_dir in
# remotion_renderer.py). The only writer into the source public/ is the
# no-date fallback path (render-time assets, public_props.json mirror,
# cover_bg.png, article images, etc.). Ignore the whole tree defensively
# so a stray render can never be committed again.
**/remotion/public/

# Claude Code
.claude/
skills-lock.json

